            "answer_text": "Brazil is, undoubtedly, \u201cThe\u201d country of South America. It\u2019s member of BRICS, it has a country risk rate of less than 300 and its inflation index is less than 5%. It has a lot of industries, development, technology and commodities like soya, beef, coffee, wheat and corn. It counts with a big service industry: Tourism. Yet, Brazil is the country of football, beautiful girls, Amazonas and exceptional beaches, but It\u2019s changing the world\u2019s perception much faster. In 20 years, Brazil will be the country of software, the country of associated services, the country of 5G and more. Only its previous business agreements can hinder its future. We refer specifically to Mercosur, an unresolved issue. ",
